paragraphs.title: Create recency column
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark


from pyspark.sql.functions import datediff, to_date, lit

split_col = pyspark.sql.functions.split(df_order_noNA['PAY_DT'], ' ')
df_date = df_order_noNA.withColumn('date', split_col.getItem(0))
#created date in  'dd-MM-yyyy' format

df_recency = df_date.withColumn("recency", datediff(to_date(lit("2011-12-15")), to_date(df_date.date, format = 'dd-MM-yyyy'))) 
#recency in days created

paragraphs.title: Get r f m for each buyer

%pyspark
import pyspark.sql.functions as func
df_recency_buyer = df_recency.groupby('BUYER_ID').agg(pyspark.sql.functions.min('recency'))
df_recency_buyer = df_recency_buyer.withColumnRenamed("BUYER_ID", "BUYER_ID_REC")
df_recency_buyer.count() 
#10727 rows

df_recency_buyer.show(5)

df_profit_buyer = df_profit.groupby('BUYER_ID').agg(pyspark.sql.functions.sum('profit'))

df_profit_buyer.show(5)

df_profit_buyer.count()

df_freq = df_combined.groupBy("BUYER_ID").agg(func.countDistinct("ORDER_ID"))

df_freq.show(10)

paragraphs.title: Join All DataFrames
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

df_combined_intermediate = df_recency_buyer.join(df_profit_buyer,[df_recency_buyer.BUYER_ID_REC == df_profit_buyer.BUYER_ID_PROF])
df_combined_final = df_combined_intermediate.join(df_freq,[df_combined_intermediate.BUYER_ID_REC == df_freq.BUYER_ID])
df_combined_final = df_combined_final.drop(*["BUYER_ID_REC","BUYER_ID_PROF"])
df_combined_final = df_combined_final.withColumnRenamed("sum(profit)", "PROFIT")
df_combined_final = df_combined_final.withColumnRenamed("min(recency)", "RECENCY")
df_combined_final = df_combined_final.withColumnRenamed("count(DISTINCT ORDER_ID)", "ORDER_COUNT")
df_combined_final_kmeans = df_combined_final.drop(*["BUYER_ID"])
df_combined_final.show()

paragraphs.title: Finding SOS to get optimal clusters
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.pyspark
from pyspark.ml.clustering import KMeans
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import ClusteringEvaluator
from pyspark.ml.linalg import Vectors
from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler


#df = spark.read.format("csv").option("inferSchema", "true").load("/__dsets/kmeans/kmeans_example.csv")

assembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=["PROFIT","RECENCY","ORDER_COUNT"], outputCol="features")

df = assembler.transform(df_combined_final_kmeans)

df.show(2)
Sum_of_squared_distances = []
K = range(2,10)
for k in K:
    kmeans = KMeans().setK(k).setSeed(1L)
    model = kmeans.fit(df)
    cost = model.computeCost(df)
    print(cost)
    Sum_of_squared_distances.append(cost)

print(Sum_of_squared_distances)

paragraphs.text:
%spark2.pyspark
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.show()

paragraphs.title: Kmeans with 5 Cluster
paragraphs.text:
%spark2.pyspark
from pyspark.ml.clustering import KMeans
from pyspark.ml.evaluation import ClusteringEvaluator
from pyspark.ml.linalg import Vectors
from pyspark.ml.feature import VectorAssembler

assembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=["PROFIT","RECENCY","ORDER_COUNT"], outputCol="features")

df = assembler.transform(df_combined_final_kmeans)

kmeans = KMeans().setK(5).setSeed(1L)
model = kmeans.fit(df)

# Results of clustering
results = model.transform(df)

results.show(2)
# Evaluate clustering by computing Silhouette score
evaluator = ClusteringEvaluator()

silhouette = evaluator.evaluate(results)
print(silhouette)

# Shows the result.
centers = model.clusterCenters()
print("Cluster Centers: ")
for center in centers:
    print(center)
